name: Theory of Computation-1
subject: TOC
syllabus: Regular expressions and finite automata, Context-free grammars and push-down automata

name: Theory of Computation-2
subject: TOC
syllabus: Regular and context-free languages, Grammar, pumping lemma, Turing machines and undecidability

name: Algorithms-1
subject: Algorithms
syllabus: Sorting, Asymptotic worst case time and space complexity, Algorithm design techniques divide-and-conquer and Searching

name: Algorithms-2
subject: Algorithms
syllabus: Binary heaps and graphs, Graph search, Greedy techniques, minimum spanning trees, shortest paths dynamic programming

name: Computer Organization and Architecture-1
subject: COA
syllabus: Instruction pipelining, Machine instructions and addressing modes and control unit

name: Computer Organization and Architecture-2
subject: COA
syllabus: ALU, data-path, Memory hierarchy cache, main memory, secondary storage and IO interface

name: Data Structures-2
subject: Data Structures
syllabus: Trees, Binary Search Trees, AVL Trees, Heaps

name: Digital Logic-1
subject: Digital Logic
syllabus: Boolean algebra, Logic gates, Combinational circuits
